# ☁️ End-to-End Azure SQL Database Analytics | Power BI Service

An end-to-end Business Intelligence project demonstrating how Azure SQL Database, SQL, Power BI Desktop, and Power BI Service work together to build a cloud-based reporting solution.

The project follows an enterprise-style analytics workflow where raw CSV data is uploaded to Azure SQL Database, cleaned and transformed using SQL, analyzed in Power BI Desktop, and finally deployed to Power BI Service as a shareable Power BI App.

This project simulates a real-world reporting workflow commonly used in organizations, where business data is stored in a cloud-hosted relational database and consumed by Power BI for interactive reporting and collaboration.

---

# 📌 Business Problem

Many organizations maintain their business data in cloud-hosted databases rather than local systems. Analysts need a reliable and centralized data source that can be securely accessed from anywhere while supporting reporting, collaboration, and deployment.

The challenge is not only to build a dashboard but also to create an end-to-end reporting pipeline that connects a cloud database with Power BI and makes the final report accessible to business users through Power BI Service.

---

# ✅ Solution

This project demonstrates an end-to-end cloud reporting workflow using Azure SQL Database as the primary data source.

The solution includes:

- Uploading raw CSV data into Azure SQL Database.
- Performing SQL-based data cleaning and preparation.
- Connecting Power BI Desktop directly to Azure SQL Database.
- Creating additional transformations using Power Query.
- Building calculated columns and business metrics using DAX.
- Designing an interactive two-page Power BI report.
- Publishing the report to Power BI Service.
- Creating a dedicated Workspace and deploying the report as a Power BI App for secure sharing and collaboration.

